International Power Plc (IPR) , the U.K.-
based utility that agreed to merge assets with GDF Suez SA last
year, said first-quarter sales rose 9 percent from a year
earlier to 4.05 billion euros ($6 billion).  The company is performing in line withe expectations and
expects growth. according to an interim management statement
today.  International Power shareholders approved the deal with GDF
Suez in December, creating the worldâ€™s second-biggest power
producer, second only to French nuclear operator Electricite de
France SA. The London-listed company has a gross operating
capacity of 70,196 megawatts, according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
